        "client_msg_id": "fc9b9c45-6aa0-46bc-b56d-a58de3430e03",
        "text": "I'm curious if anyone has thoughts on an R pre-task callback hook (executed before tasks calls similar to what `addTaskCallback()` does for post-task hooks). My motivating example is to build a better debugger, which necessarily needs to inject debug statements before code is executed.\n\nAll R debuggers today are pretty closely tied to their IDE because of this shortcoming, requiring that the IDE opaquely inject debug statements. I've tried to write an agnostic debugger over in <https:\/\/github.com\/dgkf\/debugadapter|dgkf\/debugadapter>, but it's become a real mess while working around this limitation. Its architecture would be dramatically simplified by having such a hook.\n\nSee a more detailed discussion in <https:\/\/github.com\/dgkf\/debugadapter\/issues\/4|dgkf\/debugadapter#4>, <https:\/\/github.com\/ManuelHentschel\/VSCode-R-Debugger\/issues\/156#issuecomment-990167766|ManuelHentschel\/VSCode-R-Debugger#156>",
